<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; 40 NEW 
CHARGES FILED AGAINST SERIAL RAPE SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Forty additional charges were filed Thursday against a security guard who 
allegedly abducted women from outside trendy restaurants and sexually assaulted 
them.  
</P>
<P>
 The total number of alleged victims of Sean Patrick Mitchell, 33, now stands 
at 16 and at least two more could be added, Deputy Dist. Atty.Beatriz Donoghue 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 The defendant, who is being held without bail, was initially charged with 
assaulting a dozen women over a four-week period ending in June. 
</P>
<P>
 He pleaded not guilty to 90 counts of kidnaping for robbery, kidnaping for 
sexual purposes, attempted kidnaping for robbery, attempted kidnaping for 
sexual purposes, second-degree robbery, forcible oral copulation, forcible 
rape, sodomy and attempted sodomy. The new charges are similar, Donoghue said.  
</P>
<P>
 Mitchell, who runs his own security company, was purportedly off-duty at the 
time of the alleged attacks. 
</P>
<P>
 He allegedly used a 9-millimeter handgun while abducting the women as they 
left upscale restaurants and other nightspots in Hollywood, West Hollywood and 
the Wilshire district. He generally approached women in their 20s as they were 
either getting into their cars or already in them, Donoghue said.  
</P>
<P>
 Mitchell, who was arrested June 8, allegedly kidnaped some of his victims in 
pairs. He would lock one in another room while raping the other, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
