<P>
UNWED PARENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 George Will demands the reinstitution of the stigma upon "young women who, by 
behaving irresponsibly, deserve a badge of dishonor" for becoming pregnant out 
of wedlock (Column Right, June 19). 
</P>
<P>
 Ironically, as this piece ran on Father's Day, he never once sees fit to 
mention either the word father or to suggest that similar stigmas, penalties 
and dishonors be heaped upon the young men who bear equal responsibility for 
these pregnancies. Although I share Will's concern with the number of poorly 
parented children we have in the U.S. today, I do not share his opinion that 
singling out and scapegoating women is a solution to the problem. 
</P>
<P>
