</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Executives Checking on Golden Parachutes: A growing economy and heightened 
prospects for mergers and acquisitions have executives scrambling to make sure 
their golden parachutes are in place, according to a survey by consultants 
Towers Perrin. A compensation expert at Towers Perrin said she has been getting 
lots of calls in the last six months from executives who want to make sure that 
if their company is taken over, their so-called change-in-control benefits will 
be available.Companies with cash are likely to buy other companies, the expert 
said. When they do, executives at the acquired companies can quickly be out of 
a job. The thought of that is sending them scurrying to make sure of their 
money in case they have to leave. 
</P>
