<HEADLINE>
<P>
ZUBRIN HEADS DIVING FIELD IN MISSION VIEJO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIK HAMILTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sandy Zubrin of Newport Beach will defend her title in the Southern California 
Diving Invitational, beginning today at the Marguerite Swimming and Diving 
Complex. 
</P>
<P>
 Zubrin, 17, a senior at Corona del Mar High who was this year's Division II 
Southern Section diving champion, is a heavy favorite to repeat her victory in 
the women's one- and three-meter diving and platform overall competition.Zubrin 
recently returned from competition in China, where she was third in platform at 
the Four Nations Meet in Tianjin, and 11th in the platform at the China Open. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to Zubrin, local favorites Summer Brown, Tyce Routson and 
12-year-old Erica Sorgi, who set four meet records last year, also will compete 
with more than 300 divers in the four-day meet. The Southern California Diving 
Invitational is the last important meet before the U.S. world team trials, July 
14 in St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
 Competition begins at 9 a.m. with one- and three-meter diving. Senior 
competition starts at 9 a.m. Sunday. ERIK HAMILTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA070194-0122 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 056578 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
