<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYPARK CARD CASINO OPENS THIS AFTERNOON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Hollywood Park Card Casino is scheduled to open at 1:30 p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction was completed in May but the opening was delayed until the 
company Hollywood Park chose to operate the facility, Pacific Casino 
Management, was granted a license by the state a few weeks ago. Pacific Casino 
Management is headed by former NFL figures Don Klosterman and Eddie LeBaron. 
</P>
<P>
 The casino will be open 24 hours a day, with tables for various card games, 
restaurants, a health club, stores, a sports lounge, betting windows and 
television monitors so the races can be seen. BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA070194-0125 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 056581 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
