<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPERSONICS, WARRIORS READY TO MAKE TRADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Golden State Warriors would send Sarunas Marciulionis and Byron Houston to 
Seattle in return for Ricky Pierce and the SuperSonics' No. 1 pick, Carlos 
Rogers, under a pending deal between the teams. 
</P>
<P>
 The trade hasn't been announced or formally consummated yet because of a 
freeze on new or adjusted contracts in the NBA until at least July 8.The 
moratorium is the result of a temporary restraining order issued in U.S. 
District Court in New York in response to a Players Assn. antitrust suit 
against the league. 
</P>
<P>
 Warrior President Dan Finnane confirmed Wednesday night that "something was in 
the works" but declined to be specific. 
</P>
<P>
 The San Francisco Examiner reported Thursday the deal would go through once 
the legal and technical aspects were resolved. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lakers had also tried to make a deal for Rogers, a 6-foot-11 center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
