METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SANTA CLARITA; 
RESIDENTS JOIN SEARCH FOR REAL ESTATE AGENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dozens of people in the Santa Clarita community of Val Verde joined Thursday 
with sheriff's search-and-rescue parties to look for a real estate agent who 
vanished a day earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Paula Harrington, 26, disappeared after leaving her office Wednesday afternoon 
with an unidentified man who asked to see vacant, remote houses in the 
unincorporated community of 1,500.The area is off California 126 about five 
miles northwest of the Magic Mountain theme park. 
</P>
<P>
 By late afternoon, deputies suspended their search and announced that a man 
taken into custody earlier had been cleared and released. Detectives who had 
feared that Harrington had been abducted and killed changed their approach 
after bank security cameras recorded the missing woman making a $300 withdrawal 
from an automated teller machine in Hacienda Heights. 
</P>
<P>
 "For sure it's a missing person, and possibly a kidnaping," said Lt. Donald 
Bear, a sheriff's detective. 
</P>
