<P>
N.Y. MOVES PRIMARY AHEAD OF CALIFORNIA'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a move designed to give New York more clout in presidential politics, Gov. 
Mario M. Cuomo and legislative leaders agreed Thursday to shift the state's 
primary to early March. 
</P>
<P>
 The decision comes after California moved its primary from early June to the 
fourth Tuesday in March.That would have put California before New York's 
traditional first Tuesday in April date. 
</P>
<P>
 "We will be shifting the primary to the first Tuesday in March," press 
secretary Anne Crowley said. But since a Jewish holiday falls on the first 
Tuesday in March in 1996, the primary will be held on the first Thursday that 
year, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 The presidential primary change is expected to be approved by both houses of 
the state Legislature. 
</P>
