<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DOVE CANYON; HOMEMADE BOMBS DEFUSED, TEENS HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TAMMY HYUNJOO KRESTA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two homes were evacuated Wednesday while sheriff's deputies deactivated 
explosives found in a back yard and driveway. 
</P>
<P>
 A homeowner called the Sheriff's Department about 5 p.m. after discovering 
plastic one-liter bottles containing chemicals, Lt. Daniel Martini said. 
</P>
<P>
 A hazardous-devices squad defused them and found three other bombs that 
already had exploded at the same home, causing extensive damage to the driveway 
and landscaping, Martini said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators later arrested two 16-year-old boys, one from Dove Canyon and 
one from Lake Forest, on suspicion of making the explosives, a felony. The boys 
were released to the custody of their parents. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the devices apparently were made in the boy's Dove Canyon home and 
thrown over a hillside, landing in a driveway and back yard, Lt. Daniel Martini 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was hurt, but the explosives could have caused "extensive damage" in 
the neighborhood, populated mostly by young families with children, Martini 
said.TAMMY HYUNJOO KRESTA 
</P>
</TEXT>
