<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; 16-YEAR-OLD HELD IN MAN'S SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 16-year-old youth has been arrested in connection with the slaying of a 
28-year-old man who was stabbed and shot during a confrontation Sunday 
afternoon, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager, whose name was not released because he is a minor, is suspected 
of plunging a knife into the chest of Heriberto Carachire of Santa Ana in the 
400 block of Orange Avenue.A second teen-ager, suspected of shooting the victim 
in the leg, remains at large, Lt. Robert Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
 "When we first reported this, we thought the victim had been killed by a 
gunshot," Helton said. "But an autopsy revealed that (an apparent) gunshot 
wound to the chest turned out to be a knife wound instead." 
</P>
<P>
 Carachire, who was in his car at the time of the 3 p.m. attack, managed to 
drive to his home nearby, where paramedics were called. Helton said the victim 
was a known gang member and that the confrontation was with rival gang members. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager, a resident of Santa Ana, was arrested Wednesday night as while 
walking in the 500 block of East Walnut Street. Helton said the suspect was in 
possession of a knife that authorities believe is the murder weapon. 
</P>
<P>
 "Some breaks have gone our way in this case and we've had witnesses come 
forward with good information," Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect is being held at Juvenile Hall on suspicion of murder. GREG 
HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
