<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; MAN, 21, WHO SET HIMSELF AFIRE DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TAMMY HYUNJOO KRESTA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 21-year-old man who doused himself with gasoline and then set himself on 
fire has died, police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Police identified the man as Robert James Binckley of Anaheim.He died shortly 
after 11:30 p.m. Wednesday at UCI Medical Center in Orange, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Binckley walked to Engel's AM/PM service station at 2401 W. Lincoln Ave. about 
2:15 p.m. Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 He paid for $1 worth of gas, emptied his pockets of personal possessions, sat 
down in the middle of the 16-pump station and ignited himself, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Binckley, a regular customer at Engel's, bought a packet of cigarettes along 
with the can of gasoline, said Kathy Engel, the station's owner. 
</P>
<P>
 "There were gas and flames everywhere," Engel said. "I really thought the 
place was going to go up in flames." 
</P>
<P>
 Police said bystanders put out the flames with a fire extinguisher. TAMMY 
HYUNJOO KRESTA 
</P>
</TEXT>
