<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; MEDAL OF HONOR WINNER TO SPEAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Air Force pilot who was decorated with the Medal of Honor for extraordinary 
heroism during the Vietnam War will be the guest speaker Sunday at special 
Independence Day weekend services at Grace Church, 5100 Cerritos Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Retired Col. Leo K. Thorsness, who lives in Indianola, Wash., will speak at 
the 8:30 and 10:15 a.m. services at the church.Thorsness was shot down by an 
air-to-air missile while flying his 93rd combat mission over North Vietnam in 
1967. 
</P>
<P>
 He was captured and held prisoner in North Vietnam for six years. Upon his 
release in 1973, Thorsness received the Medal of Honor from President Richard 
Nixon. 
</P>
<P>
 David Scott, an associate pastor at Grace Church, said Thorsness was invited 
to speak "because he certainly can address the price that has been paid for our 
freedom." 
</P>
<P>
 The services are open to the public. Grace Church is a nondenominational, 
evangelical institution. BILL BILLITER 
</P>
