<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; AIRPORT TO CHARGE ADDITIONAL $3 FEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACEY KAPLAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Burbank Airport will charge all outbound passengers an extra $3 fee, beginning 
Sept. 1, airport officials said.  
</P>
<P>
 The new fee, approved recently by federal officials, is expected to raise 
about $35 million over the next seven years to help pay for runway 
reconstruction, land acquisition and construction of an aircraft rescue and 
firefighting station, said Victor Gill, a Burbank Airport spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 Airlines traditionally oppose such fees because they are tacked onto ticket 
prices. But all seven airlines that fly into Burbank Airport supported the fee 
because of the advantages that would spring from the improved facilities. No 
public opposition surfaced either, Gill said.  
</P>
<P>
 Since legislation was approved four years ago, airports around the nation have 
imposed the passenger facility charge, including Los Angeles International and 
Ontario Airport. But other Southern California airports, including Long Beach 
and San Diego, do not charge the fee. TRACEY KAPLAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
