WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CONEJO VALLEY; FARMERS' MARKET TO MOVE ACROSS STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks Farmers' Market will move across the street starting 
Thursday, with 60 produce and flower vendors setting up booths in the Village 
Square Center on Moorpark Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Displaced from Janss Mall because of construction, the farmers' market will 
move permanently to the center between Hillcrest and Brazil streets. 
</P>
<P>
 The Conejo Valley market will retain its regular hours: 4 to 8 p.m. Thursdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Because the new location is more visible and offers more parking, farmers' 
market manager Karen Wetzel predicted that sales would pick up after the move.  
</P>
<P>
 But Wetzel noted that when the Ventura Farmers' Market moved in 1991, vendors 
lost many faithful customers. Sales dropped 15% after the move and stayed 
depressed for up to six months. STEPHANIE SIMON 
