<P>
MAN AND WOMAN FOUND SHOT DEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEN HALL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Deputies who stormed a condominium Thursday night after neighbors heard 
gunshots found the bodies of a man and woman, apparently the victims of a 
murder-suicide. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-age daughter of the woman had escaped the condominium through a 
window.She also had suffered an ankle wound, and was taken to Mission Hospital 
Regional Medical Center in Mission Viejo.  
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's Lt. Randy Blair said the Sheriff's Department received a call at 
6:10 p.m. about three gunshots heard at the condominium on Poveda, in a complex 
named Finisterra on the Green, which borders the Mission Viejo Country Club 
golf course. 
</P>
<P>
 As they arrived, four more shots were reported to the Sheriff's Department.  
</P>
<P>
 The SWAT team was called, and at least four nearby condominiums were 
evacuated. 
</P>
<P>
 SWAT team members broke in the front door and found two bodies lying in the 
breakfast nook, fairly close together, Blair said. 
</P>
<P>
 They also found one handgun, but they would not say where. 
</P>
