<TEXT>
<P>
 Be Our Guest: Marriott Hotels is eliminating its 75-cent credit card access 
fee for using a room telephone at some of its hotels, including several Orange 
County locations. 
</P>
<P>
 Customers also are no longer going to be charged for receiving facsimile 
copies starting today. 
</P>
<P>
 The changes are the result of research into the needs of traveling business 
executives and what they want from a hotel, Marriott officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 "By implementing these changes, we are helping them to do their job better 
while traveling," said Dave Babich, Western regional director. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the hotels participating in the program are the Marriott hotels in 
Anaheim, Fullerton, Irvine and Newport Beach and the Marriott Suites in Costa 
Mesa and Newport Beach. 
