LUTHER MEDICAL SELLS UNIT TO ILLINOIS COMPANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Catheter maker Luther Medical Products Inc. on Thursday said that it has sold 
one of its subsidiaries to Bio-logic Systems Corp. of Mundelein, Ill.Terms of 
the deal were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Luther, which has been struggling to create new distribution channels for its 
catheters, said the sale of Neuro Diagnostics Inc. is outside of the company's 
core business.  
</P>
<P>
 The subsidiary sells equipment to the neurology and rehabilitation market.  
</P>
<P>
 "It doesn't fit, and we're really not prepared to develop it," spokeswoman 
Rivian Bell said. Bio-logic Systems, on the other hand, is in a compatible 
business with Neuro Diagnostics, that is designing and marketing computerized 
medical electrodiagnostic equipment. 
