ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: ADVANCED LOGIC EXPECTS TO POST LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Advanced Logic Research Inc., a maker of personal computers, reported Thursday 
that it expects to report a net loss of less than $1.5 million for its third 
fiscal quarter ended June 30. Revenues for the quarter are expected to be 
slightly higher than the $36.1 million the company reported for the same period 
a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it expects to report final results in the last week of July. 
Gene Lu, chief executive of the Irvine-based firm, said he was disappointed 
with the third-quarter results, but he hopes new products will allow the 
company to regain its revenue momentum. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, the company expects to report revenues of $135 million, 
compared to $122.5 million for the same period a year earlier. The net loss for 
the nine months is expected to be less than $700,000, the company said, 
compared to a loss of $5.8 million a year earlier. 
</P>
