<TEXT>
<P>
 Convicted officials -- The Capitol Journal column on Monday erred in stating 
that a statewide elected official is automatically removed from office when 
convicted by a jury of a felony. The removal does not come until sentencing or 
the trial judge denies motions to set aside the verdict. There is no such 
provision for removing a legislator, who may be expelled by the lawmaker's 
house. 
</P>
